        <a title="Isaac" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Isaac" href="/user/show/59162161-isaac">Isaac</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/59162161-isaac?shelf=2020">2020</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2585771628" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10231390668279977295">After looking at Tesla&apos;s essay on the problem of increasing energy this book seemed like a logical next step. The same problem is illustrated but the emphasis is on requiring less, rather than generating more. I like the systemic answers proposed in the text, but I doubt their practicality in anything short of a future where we&apos;ve reached the level of degradation portrayed in the Mad Max movies.</span>
  <span id="freeText10231390668279977295" style="display:none">After looking at Tesla's essay on the problem of increasing energy this book seemed like a logical next step. The same problem is illustrated but the emphasis is on requiring less, rather than generating more. I like the systemic answers proposed in the text, but I doubt their practicality in anything short of a future where we've reached the level of degradation portrayed in the Mad Max movies.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10231390668279977295" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
